s. I also have to consider using `forkEvery` for tests to ensure they run independently without conflicts. But I wonder about native tests and whether they utilize the system property for the class loader. I'll need to clarify this detail!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering native executable tests**\\n\\nIt looks like native executable tests won't use a custom system loader, which raises questions about the static initialization of `FinalizableReferenceQueue` at runtime. I'm concerned that in a native image, calling `ClassLoader.getSystemClassLoader().loadClass` dynamically could lead to an `UnsupportedFeatureError`. I need to think through how this impacts my testing strategy and whether there are ways to handle this potential issue effectively. This needs careful consideration!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing test implementation**\\n\\nI’m catching errors in my existing tests, which is good. There's a potential issue with `forkEvery=1`, as it could affect test classes with the custom class loader. I need to inspect the `build.gradle` syntax and make sure to add `forkEvery = 1`. Writing a proper test is crucial, and I might include a `NativeImageSupport` catch in my test class. I wonder how naming conventions relate to the finalizer aspect and whether I need to assert for rejected states. I'll edit that as needed.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_YO0VCjkNxzY5OmweYZkv6Hpj|fc_09cce44de99c5b710169f55db7a1a081a2bd08e1854752f49f", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.google.collections/google-collections/1.0/src/testSystemClassLoader/java/com_google_collections/google_collections/FinalizerHidingSystemClassLoader.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "public final class FinalizerHidingSystemClassLoader extends URLClassLoader {\n    private static final String FINALIZER_CLASS_NAME =\n            \"com.google.common.base.internal.Finalizer\";\n\n    private static volatile boolean rejectedFinalizerLookup;\n\n    publi